STEP 1 — Load Data

Create:

backend/rag/ingest.py
Load ALL datasets

You should ingest:

docs/
incidents/
logs/
policies/
codebase/
Recommended Libraries

Use:

Purpose	Library
RAG framework	LangChain
Embeddings	Sentence Transformers
Vector DB	Chroma
STEP 2 — Chunk Documents

Very important.

Different data types require different chunking.

Docs Chunking

Chunk by:

headings
sections
Code Chunking

Chunk by:

functions
classes
APIs

NOT raw file slicing.

Logs Chunking

Chunk by:

time windows
service
Example Metadata

Store metadata like:

{
  "source": "auth-service/main.py",
  "service": "auth-service",
  "type": "code"
}

Metadata is CRITICAL.

STEP 3 — Create Embeddings

Use:

from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer

Recommended model:

all-MiniLM-L6-v2

Good enough initially.

STEP 4 — Store in ChromaDB

Example:

collection.add(
    documents=chunks,
    metadatas=metadata
)
STEP 5 — Retrieval Pipeline

Create:

backend/rag/retriever.py

This should:

embed query
retrieve top-k chunks
rerank
return context
STEP 6 — RAG QA Chain

User Query:

Why did checkout fail?

System:

retrieve logs
retrieve incident reports
retrieve deployment history
send context to LLM
